<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd3b633ba-3a6f-11f1-8dc6-9561437cf370" identifier="/us/usc/t11/s1224"><num value="1224">§ 1224.</num><heading> Confirmation hearing</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">After expedited notice, the court shall hold a hearing on confirmation of the plan. A party in interest, the trustee, or the United States trustee may object to the confirmation of the plan. Except for cause, the hearing shall be concluded not later than 45 days after the filing of the plan.</p>
